'''Mornington''' is a sea side town in [[Melbourne]], [[Victoria (Australia)|Victoria]], [[Australia]], located 57 km south-east of Melbourne's central business district. It is in the [[Local Government Areas of Victoria|Local Government Area]] of the [[Shire of Mornington Peninsula]]. Mornington's postcode is 3931, and it was first gazetted as a town in 1915.<ref>"Townsite of Mornington - Proclamation", ''Victoria Government Gazette'', [[12 May]] [[1915]], p.1915:1732.</ref>

Mornington is known for its "village" atmosphere and its beautiful beaches. Mornington is an attractive destination for shopping and features some excellent restaurants and cafes. The town centre runs into the foreshore area and local beach, which features a [[yacht club]], restaurant and park with playground facilities. Mornington is a popular destination for people from Melbourne to come down for day trips to go to the beach and enjoy the lovely atmosphere.



==Transport==
Mornington is served by two major roadways, the [[Nepean Highway]] and [[Moorooduc Highway]].

The [[Melbourne bus routes|bus routes]] 781, 784, 785 and 788 also stop at Mornington, from the terminus at [[Frankston railway station, Melbourne|Frankston Railway Station]]. From Frankston, trains run to Melbourne and other suburbs.

